summary: A new craftable armor with many variations. Four different type of dresses, many types of socks, stocking, trousers, etc. It comes with a new bow "The Eclipse" and also new type of arrows and quiver to match the armor.
descriptionHtml:
[center][color=#EBF1DD][size=4][i][font=Times New Roman]
[img]http://static-1.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-3-1410097182.jpg[/img]
[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]

[b]Important information!
[/b]
The HDT version of the mod requires [b]HDT High Heels System[/b]. Get it [b][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/36213/?]here[/url][/b]!

For the recipes to appear in the crafting interface you need to have the crafting manual in your inventory!

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Info:
[/b]
A new craftable armor with many variations. Four different type of dresses, many types of socks, stocking, trousers, etc. It comes with a new bow "The Eclipse" and also new type of arrows and quiver to match the armor.
You can find the Armor parts under the Dragonscale category and the bow and arrows under the Daedric.
All items are very powerful and the requirements to craft them are equally high.

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[youtube]CW5C9rdq0t0[/youtube] [youtube]k8EKHmRL8e8[/youtube]
[youtube]32bak8RYfpU[/youtube] [youtube]PxX2NK3TO0w[/youtube]
Thank you!
[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]

[b]Notes:
[/b]
This is the seventh armor of a series that will hopefully reach twenty four armors. I came up with the idea when I saw the Minidresses Collection mod by Tiwa44 who did an awesome job converting some of the long dresses to mini versions. So I started experimenting with his meshes to see if it's possible to convert them into armors and I came up with some very creative results.

These armors will not offer any protection in real life so don't use them at home!

There is no guarantee that I will finish all the armors but the creation has been fun so far and as long as I'm excited about this project I'll keep working on it until hopefully all armors are complete. [b]A big THANK YOU here to all of you guys that endorsed,commented or just played and keep playing using my previous mods![/b]

Below are the eight different mini dresses by Tiwa44 and my progress with the armors. I'll update the image every time something major changes. Also I came up with the names (with the help of a generator) and to my knowledge they are not used by anyone else.

[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/61012-1-1442736357.jpg[/img]
[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Acquisition:[/b]

[img]http://static-1.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1410097182.jpg[/img]
[i][font=Times New Roman]
If for any reason you can't find the book, type help "Sotteta Huntress Crafting Manual" and "player.additem xxxxxxxx 1" in the console to get the recipe book manually.
Also if you want to avoid gathering the materials (because they are many, I know :), there are enough materials inside the bag of crafting supplies to create each of the recipes once.
[/font][/i]
[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Versions:[/b]

1.00 Release

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Optional Downloads:[/b]

- A texture replacer for Apachii sky hair that changes the headband texture to mach the armor.

[i][font=Times New Roman]- A small fix for the increased white glow that some ENBs seem to produce.[/font][/i]

- German Translation

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]External Downloads:[/b]

A beautiful CBBE conversion!
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/59035/]Sotteta Huntress - CBBE - HDT BodySlide TBBP by Mitosuke[/url]

UNPB BBP, 7B Bombshell conversions!
[url=http://robton.nu/]UNPB BBP and 7B Bombshell versions by Robton[/url]

7B Conversion by RickerHK
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/59665/?]Sotteta Huntress SevenBase BombShell 7B TBBP HDT by RickerHK[/url]

The non-HDT version of the mod is also included in:
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/24684/?]UNP Clothing Merchants by Foaman[/url]

7B HDT:
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/68521/?]7B HDT Sotteta Huntress Sevenbase by gamefever[/url]

UNPB:
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/69709/?]MiniArmorsCollection - UNPB by gutris1[/url]

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b][color=#C0504D]Required mods:[/color][/b]

[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/36213/?]HDT HighHeels System by hydrogensayshdt[/url] for the HDT version.

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Known issues:[/b]
Using HDT Version without HDT High Heels System will cause your game to crash.
Due to the many transparencies of the armors, blood spills appear in places they shouldn't.
One workaround is to use the mod [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/60/?]Enhanced Blood Textures[/url] and set the wounds duration to a minimum.
If you are using HDT HighHeels System and you see weird numbers at the top left of your screen disable the debug info as shown below.

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401335443.jpg[/img] [img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1405232089.jpg[/img]

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Installation:
[/b]
a) Using the nexus mod manager
b) Manual by extracting the contents of the compressed file in the Skyrim/Data folder
[b]Important![/b] You can only have one of the two versions installed. If you want to switch between HDT and Non HDT then uninstall the one you are currently using.

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]
[b]Un-installation:
[/b]
a) Using the nexus mod manager
b) Manual by deleting Sotteta Huntress Armor.esp from the Skyrim/Data folder
and by deleting the folders that have the word [b]Sotteta Huntress[/b] inside the Skyrim/Data/Textures/DX/MiniArmorsCollection/ and Skyrim/Data/Meshes/DX/MiniArmorsCollection/ folders.

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/53846-1-1401340399.png[/img]

[/b]

[/b]
